com.esri.mo2.data.feat
Interface MapDataset

All Superinterfaces:
Dataset, GeoDataset, Searchable
All Known Subinterfaces:
FeatureClass, ImageCatalog, ImageClass, ImageServer, RemoteFeatureClass
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseFeatureClass, BaseImageClassProxy, BaseImageDirectoryCatalog, BaseImageFile, BaseImageServer, BaseMapDataset, ShapefileFeatureClass
public interface MapDataset
extends Searchable, GeoDataset

Implements a MapDataset which is a kind of GeoDataset that can be displayed on a map. This is achieved by associating a MapDataset with a DatasetLayer. To render data to the map, the DatasetLayer will call the MapDataset's search method.

The process of obtaining data in this way can be monitored by adding a DataListener to the MapDataset's list of interested listeners. The DataListener will receive DataEvents that indicate the stages that occur within data retrievals. There are 4 supported types of data that can be mapped - POINT, LINE, POLYGON and IMAGE. A MapDataset returns one type of supported data as the result of calling the search method.

See Also:
DataListener, DataEvent, DatasetLayer, Feature, Image

invalidate

public void invalidate()
Allows outside code to indicate to the MapDataset that its contents may be invalid and should be refreshed. The MapDataset responds by broadcasting a new DataEvent to the changed method of all DataListener.

fetch

public void fetch(Envelope extent,
                  double scale,
                  int width,
                  int height)
Typically called by a DatasetLayer whenever the map extent changes. The MapDataset is expected to do whatever is necessary to prepare for this change, for example, by fetching new data, or updating spatial indexes. If the MapDataset is connected with a remote server, this change may cause a retrieval of data.

If you are implementing a MapDataset that fetches data from a remote server, then you should do this by spawning a new Thread that performs the retrieval. If you are not implementing a MapDataset, but simply want to keep track of these retrievals, then you must implement a DataListener and listen for DataEvents signalled from this MapDataset.

Parameters:
extent - the new extent of the Display
scale - the new map scale in mapunits/pixel
width - the new map size in pixels across
height - the new map size in pixels down
See Also:
Searchable.search(com.esri.mo2.data.feat.QueryFilter), DatasetLayer.fetch(com.esri.mo2.cs.geom.Envelope, double, int, int)
